{
  "text": "When the body is exposed to a pathogenic microorganism, the innate immune system is activated and a response of macrophages, dendritic cells and granulocytes, and activation of pattern recognition receptor which may recognize pathogenassociated molecular patterns normally named as PAMPs are observed. Pattern recognition receptor is capable to respond successfully conducting to the overthrowing of the bacteria and resolution of inflammation process and tissue repair. This acute inflammatory process is important to the homeostasis [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] .",
